race.comment: Cracking race to start with huge pressure. DARTH INVADER (3) is a former Victorian who has been in great form for the new yard with a debut second in Queensland before scoring his maiden here by a space. Skips a grade but drops in weight and should be able to take a sit this time. Can make it two on the trot. LAVONI (7) may well be coming back from a mile but will appreciate the strong pace up front. Has been racing in far tougher company through much of the campaign. Drawn out but will drop out anyway and charge late. I'M LUCKY TWO (5) is fitter for two runs back and looks ready to win. Progressive type who can take a sit and finish strongly. CONCESSION (1) is a promising type who was in great form last time in. Fitter for three trials and rates a top chance with the right run. TURN UP THE MUSIC (17) is a super consistent galloper in good form here. Low draw and will give a sight.
